00:23:14,460 --> 00:23:17,020
I know because I took an exam in it last year.

360
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:21,020
In 1961, Edward Lorenz was running calculations for weather forecasting

361
00:23:21,020 --> 00:23:22,940
on these newfangled things called computers.

362
00:23:23,820 --> 00:23:26,700
His forecast stored data to six decimal places.

363
00:23:27,260 --> 00:23:29,660
Lorenz wanted to run the same calculations again,

364
00:23:29,660 --> 00:23:33,020
but to save time, entered the data to only three decimal places.

365
00:23:33,900 --> 00:23:36,620
He was astonished to find the outcomes differed wildly.

366
00:23:37,180 --> 00:23:39,500
Sun became storms, storms became sun.

367
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:43,900
Small changes in initial conditions made the entire system unpredictable.

368
00:23:44,860 --> 00:23:47,420
Lorenz published his findings in a paper that asked,

369
00:23:47,420 --> 00:23:51,660
does the flap of a butterfly swing in Brazil set off a tornado in Texas,

370
00:23:51,660 --> 00:23:54,060
enshrining the butterfly effect in the world's mind?

371
00:23:54,300 --> 00:23:59,500
It's also a great example of mathematicians making discoveries by being lazy.

372
00:24:00,140 --> 00:24:04,460
Chaotic systems like weather exhibit sensitive dependence on initial conditions.

373
00:24:05,020 --> 00:24:07,580
Despite being fully deterministic, that is,

374
00:24:07,580 --> 00:24:11,820
the future follows from the present by rigid laws, these systems appear random.

375
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:15,100
You can't predict them without perfect measurements,

376
00:24:15,100 --> 00:24:16,940
which are effectively impossible to obtain.

377
00:24:18,060 --> 00:24:20,140
The logistic map is one such system.

378
00:24:20,780 --> 00:24:23,740
A growth rate beyond 3.57 produces chaos.

379
00:24:24,140 --> 00:24:26,620
Your predictions add the mercy of how precisely you know

380
00:24:26,620 --> 00:24:29,740
both the starting population and the reproduction rate,

381
00:24:29,740 --> 00:24:32,860
off by even one individual and you might as well be rolling dice.

